1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The problem of finding out-branchings in directed graphs is a combinatorial problem that falls under discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a dynamic programming based algorithm for solving the problem, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The problem of finding out-branchings in directed graphs has applications in game theory, as it can be used to model decision-making processes. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The problem of finding out-branchings in directed graphs can be viewed as a geometric problem, where the directed graph can be represented as a set of points and the out-branching as a spanning tree. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the computational complexity of the problem and shows that it is fixed parameter tractable, which falls under the domain of computational complexity.
